*The provided service daemon template can be used to register Stratos/CEP/MB/.. as Linux services

1. Set USER, PRODUCT_CODE, CARBON_HOME, CMD and JAVA_HOME in daemon_service file
2. Set process name in top commented section (processname: <SERVICE_NAME>)
3. Rename the file to <SERVICE_NAME>
4. Copy the <SERVICE_NAME> file to /etc/init.d/ of the host instance where the service needs to be registered
5. Set '0755' permission to the file (chmod +x <SERVICE_NAME>)	
6. Run 'chkconfig --add <SERVICE_NAME>'

